	    <p>It seems as though our poster who is railing about the President has no clue what Federal law is surrounding the PResident and his family. If he did, he would know that Federal laws are in place specifically to prevent this sort of thing from happening. In Virginia, however, it is perfectly legal for elected leaders to accept any and all manner of bribe, uh, er, gift - as long as it's reported. McDonnell seems to be playing fast and loose with the "family" loophole in Virginia law. To equate this with the President, whether it's Obama or Bush or whomever, is just another ignorant partisant rant that only points out who little the poster knows about the law and the real world. Back away from the Fox News box. It's makes you look stupid.</p>
